&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.five9.com/sites/default/files/2025-02/five9-logo.svg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;100&quot; style=&quot;max-width: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us in bringing joy to customer experience. &amp;nbsp;Five9 is a leading provider of cloud contact center software, bringing the power of cloud innovation to customers worldwide. &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Living our values everyday results in our team-first culture and enables us to innovate, grow, and thrive while enjoying the journey together. We celebrate diversity and foster an inclusive environment, empowering our employees to be their authentic selves.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic and enthusiastic &lt;strong&gt;Apprentice - HR&lt;/strong&gt; to support our Human Resources team. This role is ideal for fresh graduates who are passionate about building a career in HR. The individual will primarily support new joiner induction, employee engagement initiatives, and HRBP analytics / ops while gaining hands-on experience across HR functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New Joiner Induction &amp;amp; Onboarding&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Welcome and assist new employees on their joining day&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coordinate induction schedules and logistics (conference rooms, materials, system access)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Facilitate or support induction sessions and company orientation programs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Act as the first point of contact for new joiners for any queries&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employee Engagement Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assist in planning and executing employee engagement activities and events&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coordinate logistics for town halls, celebrations, and team-building initiatives&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support employee surveys, feedback collection, and analysis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Help drive initiatives that enhance employee experience and workplace culture&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HR Operations &amp;amp; Coordination&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prepare reports and dashboards related to onboarding and engagement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coordinate with internal stakeholders (HRBP, Admin, IT, Payroll) for seamless operations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provide administrative support to the HR team as required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eligibility Criteria&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Human Resources, Business Administration, or related field&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Freshers encouraged to apply&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong interest in Human Resources and people management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Skills &amp;amp; Competencies&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good communication and interpersonal skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong coordination and organizational abilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Attention to detail and problem-solving mindset&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Basic knowledge of MS Office (Excel, PowerPoint, Word)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Willingness to learn and take initiative&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Learning &amp;amp; Development Opportunities&l

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.five9.com/sites/default/files/2025-02/five9-logo.svg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;100&quot; style=&quot;max-width: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us in bringing joy to customer experience. &amp;nbsp;Five9 is a leading provider of cloud contact center software, bringing the power of cloud innovation to customers worldwide. &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Living our values everyday results in our team-first culture and enables us to innovate, grow, and thrive while enjoying the journey together. We celebrate diversity and foster an inclusive environment, empowering our employees to be their authentic selves.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a high-potential &lt;strong&gt;Product Manager Apprentice&lt;/strong&gt; to join our Product Management team working on next-generation &lt;strong&gt;Contact Center as a Service (CCaaS)&lt;/strong&gt; platforms. This role is designed for early-career professionals who are passionate about building enterprise SaaS products and want hands-on exposure to &lt;strong&gt;AI-driven customer experience technologies and modern cloud-native architectures&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Product Manager Apprentice, you will work closely with&amp;nbsp; Product Managers, Engineering, UX, Data Science, and GTM teams to define, build, and scale features across our CCaaS product lines — including &lt;strong&gt;AI-powered voice, digital, analytics, automation, workforce management and integrations platforms&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a learning-intensive role that provides real ownership, structured mentorship, and exposure to the full product lifecycle in a fast-growing SaaS environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Discovery &amp;amp; Strategy Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in researching customer problems across contact center domains such as &lt;strong&gt;Inbound&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;outbound campaigns, agent experience, AI automation, analytics, Quality Management, Workforce Management, and integrations&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze market trends in &lt;strong&gt;CCaaS, AI in CX, cloud communications, and SaaS platforms&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support product managers in defining product vision, value propositions, and roadmap priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI &amp;amp; Data-Driven Product Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with AI/ML teams on features involving &lt;strong&gt;speech-to-text, NLP, LLMs, conversation intelligence, automation, and predictive analytics&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help translate AI capabilities into real-world customer use cases and measurable business outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to defining product requirements for AI-enabled workflows and decisioning systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements &amp;amp; Delivery Execution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in creating &lt;strong&gt;Product Requirement Documents (PRDs), user stories, and acceptance criteria&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with engineering teams using Agile/Scrum methodologies to support sprint planning, backlog grooming, and release execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in feature demos, UAT coordination, and release readiness activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Modern SaaS Platform Exposure&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gain hands-on experience with &lt;strong&gt;cloud-native, multi-tenant SaaS architectures, APIs, microservices, security, and scalability concepts&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support integration initiatives

